  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Rapid response for the West Bank health-care waste management in response to COVID-19 outbreak</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main purpose of this action is to  guarantee a proper management of health-care waste, avoiding wastes from being scattered indiscriminately around medical buildings and their grounds and reducing the likelihood of secondary infections. 
This action will therefore strengthen the government and humanitarian intervention by the following actionts: assessment of infectious waste handling, development of online technical training/SOP and establishment of an emergency centralized system for infectious waste collection and safe disposal according to WHO minimum requirements for the North area of the West Bank. The project will be implemented in Jenin, Tubas, Nablus, Tulkarem, Salfit and Qalqilya whereas the SOP will be available and spread in all West Bank</narrative>
  </description>
